<p>There is an example in the reference guide saying you can configure Zend_Form_Element_Captcha with an array like this:</p>

<p>$element = new Zend_Form_Element_Captcha('foo', array(
    'label' =&gt; "Please verify you're a human",
    'captcha' =&gt; 'Figlet',
    'captchaOptions' =&gt; array(
        'captcha' =&gt; 'Figlet',
        'wordLen' =&gt; 6,
        'timeout' =&gt; 300,
    ),
));</p>

<p>In case you are using an Image adapter and provide configuration options as 'captchaOptions' - all of them will be renderend in the final html output that exposes your full server path and some other configuration options and paths that should not be exposed.</p>

